WEBVTT

00:00:32.178 --> 00:00:35.056
THE JUDGE RETURNS

00:00:35.765 --> 00:00:38.225
EPISODE 12

00:00:54.367 --> 00:00:55.451
Please open your arms.

00:01:03.125 --> 00:01:04.168
Your phone, please.

00:01:08.839 --> 00:01:09.882
Please follow me.

00:01:21.769 --> 00:01:22.770
Hello, sir.

00:01:26.482 --> 00:01:27.942
We've met, haven't we?

00:01:28.567 --> 00:01:29.610
Yes.

00:01:31.070 --> 00:01:34.031
I heard you'd be taking
Tae-sik's case in court.

00:01:34.824 --> 00:01:36.200
That's new to me.

00:01:37.660 --> 00:01:39.078
You'll hear about it soon enough.

00:01:44.917 --> 00:01:47.336
The limit is 500 million won per year.

00:01:57.847 --> 00:02:00.808
I'd like you to sentence him
to five years in prison.

00:02:03.436 --> 00:02:05.813
And he'll get the three-and-five sentence
in the appeals trial.

00:02:05.896 --> 00:02:07.773
A three-year sentence, suspended for five.

00:02:09.024 --> 00:02:11.527
That's nothing new, you know?

00:02:13.863 --> 00:02:16.949
Unless you want to check
how I spend every penny of this

00:02:17.032 --> 00:02:19.618
you can give the money to me in cash
after the trial.

00:02:19.702 --> 00:02:21.036
No need to leave traces.

00:02:27.084 --> 00:02:28.085
Have a good day.

00:02:31.547 --> 00:02:32.673
My phone, please.

00:02:39.972 --> 00:02:41.974
I met Mr. Jang Yong-hyeon.

00:02:42.475 --> 00:02:44.685
He told me to sentence Tae-sik
to five years in jail

00:02:44.769 --> 00:02:47.188
while handing a credit card
with a 500 million won limit.

00:02:49.190 --> 00:02:51.275
He can be so impatient.

00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:53.068
Five years in the first trial

00:02:53.152 --> 00:02:55.654
and three years in prison
with five years on suspension in the next.

00:02:55.946 --> 00:02:57.740
That's the magic formula
for conglomerates.

00:02:58.532 --> 00:03:00.034
- So?
- Tae-sik's case involves

00:03:00.117 --> 00:03:02.495
a few hundred billion won
with the illicit loans and slush funds.

00:03:02.578 --> 00:03:05.289
It's not a case to be handled
by a single-judge criminal court.

00:03:05.706 --> 00:03:08.709
I didn't answer him,
as I didn't have your permission yet.

00:03:10.795 --> 00:03:13.881
Tae-sik will soon be indicted
while in custody.

00:03:15.174 --> 00:03:17.802
A panel of judges will take on the case,
so sort it out there.

00:03:18.552 --> 00:03:20.596
Don't worry about the lead judge.

00:03:20.679 --> 00:03:22.765
Conduct a legal review
and finalize the sentencing order.

00:03:24.058 --> 00:03:26.811
Oh, you might as well be promoted
to a Presiding Judge for this.

00:03:29.438 --> 00:03:30.648
But I'm not sure

00:03:31.398 --> 00:03:33.275
how long his sentence should be.

00:03:35.444 --> 00:03:38.197
Sin-jin has no interest
in giving Yong-hyeon what he wants.

00:03:38.280 --> 00:03:40.199
Give me an answer,
and that'll be my verdict.

00:03:41.450 --> 00:03:42.451
Didn't you hear me?

00:03:43.410 --> 00:03:45.329
I thought I'd already answered you.

00:03:50.751 --> 00:03:52.044
I'll follow the law.

00:03:52.711 --> 00:03:54.088
But wouldn't that cause issues?

00:03:54.171 --> 00:03:56.674
Don't look for justice
through questions and debates.

00:03:57.132 --> 00:03:58.467
Show me your justice

00:03:58.884 --> 00:04:01.095
the equity and common sense

00:04:03.013 --> 00:04:05.224
that everyone knows in their hearts.

00:04:07.852 --> 00:04:10.396
I was going to get rid of them all

00:04:11.021 --> 00:04:12.982
once I became the leader of Suojae,
anyway.

00:04:16.277 --> 00:04:17.278
You may go.

00:04:19.363 --> 00:04:20.406
Yes, sir.

00:04:30.165 --> 00:04:31.250
Have you decided?

00:04:35.713 --> 00:04:39.174
Mr. Jang has more accounts under an alias,
aside from those at Jeongdaun.

00:04:39.258 --> 00:04:41.218
I'll give you half of the funds there.

00:04:41.302 --> 00:04:43.679
So, 20 billion won. But promise me...

00:04:48.350 --> 00:04:49.852
I'll be safe

00:04:50.477 --> 00:04:52.187
after all this.

00:04:54.023 --> 00:04:55.065
Of course.

00:04:55.858 --> 00:04:57.610
Tell Yong-hyeon

00:04:58.611 --> 00:05:01.030
exactly what he wants to hear.

00:05:03.741 --> 00:05:06.076
Let Tae-sik take the fall
for the slush funds

00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:08.662
but you take care of the illicit loans

00:05:08.746 --> 00:05:10.956
without Tae-sik hearing about them.

00:05:15.544 --> 00:05:18.380
Think of it as being extra loyal.

00:05:19.423 --> 00:05:20.591
Come on.

00:05:21.091 --> 00:05:23.010
Open an account.

00:05:23.886 --> 00:05:26.513
I'll give you a bonus.

00:05:27.097 --> 00:05:28.474
Sir...

00:05:29.433 --> 00:05:33.062
I might lose my license to practice law.

00:05:36.023 --> 00:05:39.109
You don't earn much
with that license, anyway.

00:05:40.319 --> 00:05:43.113
I'm your pot of gold, not your license.

00:05:44.114 --> 00:05:45.282
Me, Jang Yong-hyeon.

00:05:46.575 --> 00:05:47.826
Trust me.

00:05:48.577 --> 00:05:50.537
Judge Lee has been assigned to the case

00:05:50.621 --> 00:05:53.332
and Mr. Kang told him to sentence Tae-sik
to five years in jail.

00:05:55.709 --> 00:05:57.211
As he should.

00:05:58.003 --> 00:06:00.172
Make sure your testimony matches

00:06:00.255 --> 00:06:02.257
that of the loan officer
at Jeongdaun Savings.

00:06:02.967 --> 00:06:06.136
And make sure Tae-sik isn't involved
in the illicit loans.

00:06:06.804 --> 00:06:08.347
- You know what I mean?
- Yes, sir.

00:06:10.140 --> 00:06:12.726
You're basically family to S Group now.

00:06:13.978 --> 00:06:14.979
Congratulations.

00:06:15.813 --> 00:06:18.023
- Thank you, sir.
- Sure.

00:06:39.420 --> 00:06:43.173
We're representing Mr. Jang,
the CEO of S Shopping, in court.

00:06:43.799 --> 00:06:46.510
Han-young will be on the panel of judges.

00:06:49.722 --> 00:06:50.931
He may be an associate judge

00:06:51.015 --> 00:06:54.059
but he'll dictate the verdict.

00:06:55.811 --> 00:06:58.230
Make a team and take on Tae-sik's case.

00:07:00.274 --> 00:07:01.275
Me?

00:07:02.735 --> 00:07:04.319
- Really?
- Why are you so surprised?

00:07:04.403 --> 00:07:06.071
It's about time you get some experience.

00:07:07.281 --> 00:07:09.158
Maybe start dressing up, too.

00:07:12.619 --> 00:07:14.997
Are you on the panel of judges
for Mr. Jang's trial?

00:07:16.081 --> 00:07:18.417
Haenal Law Firm is really in
on all the secrets.

00:07:18.584 --> 00:07:19.710
Of course.

00:07:20.461 --> 00:07:22.379
Dad wants me to make a team
to represent him.

00:07:23.881 --> 00:07:26.717
Eat up. It's on me today.

00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:29.470
If this is your bribe for Mr. Jang's case,
I don't want it.

00:07:30.929 --> 00:07:34.183
Have you already forgotten about my help
with the Miracle scam?

00:07:34.266 --> 00:07:37.394
You asked for a meal at my house
in return for your help

00:07:37.478 --> 00:07:39.146
which you got.

00:07:39.229 --> 00:07:42.191
That means neither of us owes anything
to each other, Ms. Yu.

00:07:42.941 --> 00:07:44.318
Fine.

00:07:44.401 --> 00:07:45.736
I get it.

00:07:46.028 --> 00:07:48.864
But why do you keep calling me "Ms. Yu"?
It's like we're strangers.

00:07:48.989 --> 00:07:50.824
Are you distancing yourself from me?

00:07:53.035 --> 00:07:54.453
Seriously.

00:07:54.536 --> 00:07:55.871
I just want to...

00:07:55.954 --> 00:07:57.915
Gosh, I wish I could just punch you once.

00:07:57.998 --> 00:07:59.124
Just one punch, please?

00:07:59.208 --> 00:08:01.919
Why? Was the slap on our first date
not enough?

00:08:02.419 --> 00:08:03.712
I should've hit you more then.

00:08:03.796 --> 00:08:05.380
Don't take Tae-sik's case.

00:08:05.464 --> 00:08:07.800
I've already agreed to take it.

00:08:07.883 --> 00:08:11.512
Mr. Kang is behind Han-young joining
the panel of judges.

00:08:11.595 --> 00:08:14.139
He's got S Group's back.

00:08:14.807 --> 00:08:16.892
It'll just be
a five-year sentence in prison

00:08:17.810 --> 00:08:18.977
so just don't mess up.

00:08:19.186 --> 00:08:20.729
Aren't you sentencing him
to five years in jail?

00:08:22.564 --> 00:08:24.399
We'll bust S Group entirely

00:08:24.483 --> 00:08:26.819
starting from Tae-sik
to his father's slush funds.

00:08:26.902 --> 00:08:29.530
We're shaking up the whole conglomerate,
so don't get involved.

00:08:30.447 --> 00:08:31.698
Really?

00:08:37.329 --> 00:08:38.580
Yes, Lee Han-young speaking.

00:08:40.457 --> 00:08:43.919
I made Yi-seok the Chief Justice,
as you suggested.

00:08:44.002 --> 00:08:47.005
Looks like you'll soon have
the Chief Justice as your legal advisor.

00:08:47.548 --> 00:08:48.632
Congratulations.

00:08:53.011 --> 00:08:54.054
I once ran

00:08:54.847 --> 00:08:56.557
like there was no tomorrow.

00:08:57.141 --> 00:08:59.852
Are you a professional runner?

00:08:59.935 --> 00:09:00.936
No.

00:09:02.855 --> 00:09:04.857
If you're not a professional

00:09:05.691 --> 00:09:07.526
why are you running so hard?

00:09:10.237 --> 00:09:11.238
What?

00:09:15.868 --> 00:09:17.411
I couldn't answer him.

00:09:17.494 --> 00:09:19.705
I didn't know why I was running so hard.

00:09:21.081 --> 00:09:25.294
And I definitely didn't know
when to stop or where I was.

00:09:27.045 --> 00:09:29.548
But I started living a different life

00:09:31.383 --> 00:09:34.094
and finally realized
why I had to keep running.

00:09:38.557 --> 00:09:40.517
I know why I have to keep running now.

00:09:42.436 --> 00:09:44.688
To become a better person

00:09:46.732 --> 00:09:48.066
for my family

00:09:49.735 --> 00:09:51.695
and the person I love.

00:09:52.863 --> 00:09:54.323
And for myself.

00:10:05.959 --> 00:10:07.127
What kind of a life

00:10:09.546 --> 00:10:11.048
did you live before?

00:10:12.966 --> 00:10:14.259
Someone said

00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:16.011
I was garbage.

00:10:16.637 --> 00:10:17.930
"Garbage"?

00:10:18.722 --> 00:10:21.308
Come on. There's no way.

00:10:25.520 --> 00:10:27.481
Don't take Tae-sik's case.

00:10:27.564 --> 00:10:30.609
Let your brother or sister take it.
Let them be greedy.

00:10:31.735 --> 00:10:32.736
Is it

00:10:33.528 --> 00:10:35.322
really that bad of a case?

00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:41.745
What do you want to do

00:10:42.663 --> 00:10:44.790
once the law firm becomes yours?

00:10:50.295 --> 00:10:51.296
Well...

00:10:55.092 --> 00:10:56.343
That's...

00:11:16.196 --> 00:11:18.073
Why didn't I think of that?

00:11:31.461 --> 00:11:32.462
Let's go.

00:11:32.713 --> 00:11:33.714
Let's run!

