SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

00:13:52.269 --> 00:13:54.312
LETTER OF INDICTMENT
YOU ARE INDICTED AS STATED BELOW

00:13:56.398 --> 00:13:57.983
PRINT

00:14:08.160 --> 00:14:10.912
CHIEF PROSECUTOR KANG JI-HWAN

00:14:10.996 --> 00:14:12.497
DETAILS REGARDING THE DEFENDANT

00:14:13.748 --> 00:14:14.791
What's this?

00:14:15.208 --> 00:14:17.169
He takes money from elders
who collect scraps

00:14:17.252 --> 00:14:19.671
and kids who collect every penny they get

00:14:19.754 --> 00:14:21.798
for his drinking parties every night.

00:14:21.882 --> 00:14:24.718
Don't you know
giving non-profits a bad rep like this

00:14:24.801 --> 00:14:27.137
makes people stop donating,
even to good charities?

00:14:27.637 --> 00:14:30.474
Think of it as an opportunity cost
for our society and stop here.

00:14:30.557 --> 00:14:31.558
Our society?

00:14:32.434 --> 00:14:34.519
For whom in our society?

00:14:35.854 --> 00:14:38.148
A significant portion
of the donations goes

00:14:39.649 --> 00:14:42.694
to a borrowed-name account
of an unidentified person.

00:14:42.777 --> 00:14:44.696
I told you to stop, alright?

00:14:59.794 --> 00:15:02.297
Do you get a share of the donations, too?

00:15:03.840 --> 00:15:05.133
Cheol-woo!

00:15:09.763 --> 00:15:11.389
Do you want to get fired right now?

00:15:11.973 --> 00:15:14.017
You want me to leave you
with absolutely nothing?

00:15:14.100 --> 00:15:15.936
Why can't you just say it's not true?

00:15:16.019 --> 00:15:18.063
It's not true, you bastard!

00:15:18.563 --> 00:15:19.648
Who gets the money, then?

00:15:22.692 --> 00:15:25.612
Why are you asking me?

00:15:27.572 --> 00:15:29.074
Get this out of my face

00:15:29.741 --> 00:15:31.535
unless you want to get fired right now.

00:15:44.339 --> 00:15:45.882
Our country's prosecution is rotten.

00:15:45.966 --> 00:15:47.551
Why? Were you told you'd be fired?

00:15:48.969 --> 00:15:51.012
- Did you spy on me?
- I didn't need to.

00:15:51.680 --> 00:15:52.931
Here comes another one.

00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:02.732
Daejin Daily says

00:16:02.816 --> 00:16:04.901
we can't publish a word about this.

00:16:04.985 --> 00:16:09.322
And the reporters from other agencies ran
the minute I mentioned the foundation.

00:16:10.115 --> 00:16:13.827
They don't want to tackle Seonjin
because Gwang-to is the face.

00:16:14.995 --> 00:16:17.998
Does that make any sense to you?

00:16:18.331 --> 00:16:21.209
Those who don't know
what Gwang-to is really like think

00:16:21.293 --> 00:16:24.379
he's just a kind, former President
who always thinks of his people.

00:16:25.547 --> 00:16:28.300
Cheer up.
You knew it wasn't going to work.

00:16:28.383 --> 00:16:29.718
- No, I didn't!
- No, I didn't!

00:16:29.801 --> 00:16:31.386
I was sure we could do this.

00:16:31.469 --> 00:16:32.637
We found fraudulent ledgers!

00:16:32.721 --> 00:16:34.347
How can we not investigate it?

00:16:37.809 --> 00:16:40.437
Did you tell us to do this,
knowing we'd fail?

00:16:40.520 --> 00:16:42.480
Did you really?

00:16:42.981 --> 00:16:47.777
The corrupt are resilient.
It only hardens under outside pressure.

00:16:47.861 --> 00:16:50.530
To break it, we have to trigger
a fracture from the inside.

00:16:51.531 --> 00:16:53.950
Now that they know
the press and the prosecution are on it

00:16:54.034 --> 00:16:55.493
they'll start to get on it, too.

00:16:55.910 --> 00:16:57.287
Then, once they realize

00:16:57.370 --> 00:16:59.372
things aren't going as they'd expected

00:16:59.456 --> 00:17:01.124
they'll start to split up.

00:17:01.207 --> 00:17:04.711
Then, the corrupt will finally break.

00:17:05.754 --> 00:17:07.672
You used us as baits.

00:17:07.756 --> 00:17:09.799
He definitely did.

00:17:09.883 --> 00:17:11.551
I guess I'm the hook.

00:17:11.635 --> 00:17:13.762
Are you the worm?

00:17:14.179 --> 00:17:15.972
- Don't put it like that.
- No, krill.

00:17:16.765 --> 00:17:18.350
I don't know how he got it

00:17:18.433 --> 00:17:19.434
but Prosecutor Park has

00:17:19.517 --> 00:17:22.145
the Seonjin Foundation's
fraudulent ledgers.

00:17:23.021 --> 00:17:24.522
I don't think he's going to stop.

00:17:26.775 --> 00:17:29.944
We should've gotten rid of him
when we got rid of Jeong-tae.

00:17:31.696 --> 00:17:33.823
It'll get messy if he keeps this up.

00:17:36.201 --> 00:17:38.370
Should we get on it now?

00:17:39.329 --> 00:17:42.332
I hear Cheol-woo is asking
to investigate the foundation.

00:17:44.042 --> 00:17:46.961
If anything happens now,
the whole world will watch them.

00:17:52.092 --> 00:17:53.843
We have no choice

00:17:55.553 --> 00:17:56.888
but to face it.

00:18:13.321 --> 00:18:14.406
We've never met, have we?

00:18:16.366 --> 00:18:17.867
No, but I know who you are.

00:18:29.254 --> 00:18:30.714
There's an opportunity cost

00:18:31.256 --> 00:18:32.841
to establishing justice.

00:18:36.219 --> 00:18:39.347
Does it also cost people's lives?

00:18:44.060 --> 00:18:45.770
That's not nice.

00:18:46.646 --> 00:18:49.232
I didn't know there was a price tag
to achieving justice.

00:18:53.153 --> 00:18:55.155
What's justice to you, Mr. Park?

00:18:55.822 --> 00:18:57.949
Arresting all bad guys, no matter what.

00:18:58.366 --> 00:18:59.743
That's what justice is to me.

00:19:00.952 --> 00:19:02.162
I like how simple it is.

00:19:03.705 --> 00:19:06.666
You want to strike the Seonjin Foundation?
I can help you.

00:19:08.752 --> 00:19:11.671
Arrest the Chairman
for embezzlement and breach of trust.

00:19:12.714 --> 00:19:15.550
Would that establish justice for you?

00:19:17.677 --> 00:19:20.972
He's using the Chairman as a sacrifice
for the foundation.

00:19:23.308 --> 00:19:24.434
What do you think?

00:19:27.979 --> 00:19:30.523
Let's accept the sacrifice first,
as Sin-jin wants.

00:19:31.149 --> 00:19:32.192
And then?

00:19:32.567 --> 00:19:34.944
We'll sprinkle salt
before the wound heals.

00:19:55.715 --> 00:19:57.926
Kwak Sang-cheol,
the opposition party's hitman.

00:19:58.384 --> 00:19:59.844
He's known as the "crazy dog"

00:19:59.928 --> 00:20:02.555
for all his bluntly honest whistleblowing
and slander.

00:20:05.099 --> 00:20:06.768
Mr. Lee Han-young?

00:20:08.144 --> 00:20:09.604
Thank you for coming.

00:20:11.815 --> 00:20:15.652
The future son-in-law of Haenal
wants to discuss party nominations.

00:20:15.735 --> 00:20:17.695
Who would say no to that?

00:20:18.947 --> 00:20:20.573
I'm guessing it's not for free.

00:20:21.825 --> 00:20:23.660
I need you to attack someone.

00:20:25.703 --> 00:20:28.873
I guess Haenal has an enemy?

00:20:28.957 --> 00:20:31.501
